cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.MA 

This paper deals with the optimization of energy and information access points in wireless powered communication networks, which involves the study of wireless information and power transmissions. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization techniques, which suggests that it could belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The study of energy harvesting and communication performance requirements of wireless devices could also place it in cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the simulation results involve the use of multimedia, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
